onald O'Connor]]) dies, he leaves his carnival to his widow Angel ([[Traci Lords]]). Bandit helps her face off against some shady characters smuggling stolen silver ingots hidden in the carnival.\n}}\n}}</onlyinclude>\n\n==Home media==\nOn October 12, 2010, [[Universal Pictures Home Entertainment]] released all four television films on [[DVD]] along with the ''Smokey and the Bandit'' trilogy as part of '''''Smokey and the Bandit: The 7-Movie Outlaw Collection'''''.<ref>[https://www.amazon.com/Smokey-Bandit-7-Movie-Outlaw-Collection/dp/B003VRJ89S/ref=sr_1_3?s=movies-tv&ie=UTF8&qid=1536593748&sr=1-3&keywords=smokey+and+the+bandit+7-movie Smokey and the Bandit The 7-Movie Outlaw Collection at Amazon.com]</ref>\n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n==See also==\n*''[[Smokey and the Bandit]]''\n*''[[Smokey and the Bandit II]]''\n*''[[Smokey and the Bandit Part 3]]''\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb title|0109205|Bandit: Bandit Goes Country}}\n*{{IMDb title|0109207|Bandit: Bandit Bandit}}\n*{{IMDb title|0109210|Bandit: Beauty and the Bandit}}\n*{{IMDb title|0109209|Bandit: Bandit's Silver Angel}}\n\n{{Hal Needham}}\n{{Smokey and the Bandit}}\n[[Category:1994 television films]]\n[[Category:1990s action films]]\n[[Category:1990s prequel films]]\n[[Category:American films]]\n[[Category:American television films]]\n[[Category:American action comedy films]]\n[[Category:American film series]]\n[[Category:Film series]]\n[[Category:Film spin-offs]]\n[[Category:Television prequel films]]\n[[Category:First-run syndicated television programs in the United States]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Hal Needham]]\n[[Category:Action Pack (Universal Television)]]\n[[Category:Smokey and the Bandit]]\n", "name_user": "Moe1810", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bandit_(film_series)"}
{"title_page": "Nepalis", "text_new": "{{pp-move|small=yes}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{more references}}\n'''Nepalis''' (singular:'''Nepali''', synonym:'''Nepalese'''; {{lang-ne|\u0928\u0947\u092a\u093e\u0932\u0940}}) are the people associated with the country of [[Nepal]]. The term usually refers to the [[Nepali nationality law|citizens]] and nationals of Nepal, or the native speakers of the Nepali language. It is also used in reference to the people of Nepali origin or of ethnicities strongly associated with Nepal irrespective of their citizenship or native language.\n\n==Nepali citizens and nationals==\nNepali nationals number around 30 Million, with six million of them residing in India,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indembkathmandu.gov.in/page/about-india-nepal-relations/|title=Embassy of India, Kathmandu, Nepal : About India-Nepal Relations|website=www.indembkathmandu.gov.in|access-date=2020-04-17}}</ref> and one million more scattered around the world. They are multicultural, multiethnic and multilinguistic group that speak [[Languages of Nepal|123 languages]] as recorded in [[2011 Nepal census]].\n\nThe population ranking of 125 Nepali castes/ethnic groups as per the [[2011 Nepal census]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://unstats.un.org/unsD/demographic/sources/census/wphc/Nepal/Nepal-Census-2011-Vol1.pdf|title=Nepal Census 2011}}</ref>\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\" style=\"text-align: right;\"\n! style=\"text-align:left\" | Rank\n! Caste/ethnic groups\n! Population\n! Percentage composition\n\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left\" | 1\n| [[Chhetri]]\n| 4,398,053\n| 16.60%\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left\" | 2\n| [[Bahun|Hill Brahman/Bahun]]\n| 3,226,903\n| 12.18%\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left\" | 3\n| [[Magar people|Magar]]\n| 1,887,733\n| 7.12%\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left\" | 4\n| [[Tharu people|Tharu]]\n| 1,737,470\n| 6.56%\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left\" | 5\n| [[Tamang people|Tamang]]\n| 1,539,830\n| 5.81%\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left\" | 6\n| [[Newar]] \n| 1,321,933\n| 4.99%\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left\" | 7\n| [[Kami (caste)|Kami]]\n| 1,258,554\n| 4.75%\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left\" | 8\n| [[Nepali Muslims]] \n| 1,164,255\n| 4.39%\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left\" | 9\n|[[Yadav]]\n| 1,054,458\n| 3.98%\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left\" |10\n| [[Rai (ethnic group)|Rai]]\n| 620,004\n| 2.34%\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left\" | 11\n| [[Gurung people|Gurung]]\n| 522,641\n|1.97%\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left\" |12\n| [[Damai|Damai/Dholi]]\n|472,862\n|1.78%\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left\" | 13\n| [[Thakuri]]\n|425,623\n|1.61%\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left\" | 14\n| [[Limbu people|Limbu]]\n|387,300\n|1.46%\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left\" | 15\n| [[Sarki (ethnic group)|Sarki]]\n|374,816\n|1.41%\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left\" | 16\n| [[Teli]]\n|369,688\n|1.40%\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left\" | 17\n| [[Chamar|Chamar/Harijan/Ram]]\n|335,893\n|1.27%\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left\" | 18\n|[[Kushwaha|Koiri/Kushwaha]]\n|306,393\n|1.16%\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left\" | 19\n| [[Musahar]]\n|234,490\n|0.89%\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left\" | 20\n|[[Kurmi]]\n|231,129\n|0.87%\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left\" | 21\n|[[Sanyasi|Sanyasi/Dasnami]]\n|227,822\n|0.86%\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left\" | 22\n|[[Dhanuk]]\n|219,808\n|0.83%\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left\" | 23\n|[[Dusadh|Dusadh/Pasawan/Pasi]]\n|208,910\n|0.79%\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left\" | 24\n|[[Raute people|Raute]]\n| 618\n| 0.00%\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left\" | 25\n| Nurang\n| 278\n| 0.00%\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left\" | 26\n|[[Kusunda people|Kusunda]]\n| 273\n| 0.00%\n|-\n|-style=\"text-align:left\" |27\n|27\n|Hyolmo/ Yolmo\n\n| style=\"text-align:left\" | 1,50,000\n|1%\n|-\n|\n|Others\n|132321\n|0.7%\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left\" | -\n|'''Total'''\n| 26,494,504\n| 100.00%\n|}\n{{clear}}\n==Native Nepali speakers==\nThere are around 16 million native speakers of the Nepali language\u2014around 12 million in Nepal, three million in India, and about a million more including populations in Bhutan and other countries in the region, as well as the Nepalese diaspora around the world. \n\n==Others==\nOther people who are neither citizens or nationals of Nepal nor native speakers of the Nepali language, may still be referred to as Nepalis, based on their connection with the country or the Nepali language. The people belonging to ethnicities found in Nepal and using Nepali as the lingua franca, and other descendants of the people of Nepal or speakers of the Nepali language are also referred to as Nepalis.\n\n==See also==\n* [[Languages of Nepal]]\n* [[List of Nepali people]]\n* [[Music of Nepal]]\n* [[Religion in Nepal]]\n{{notelist}}\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Nepalese people| ]]\n[[Category:Ethnic groups divided by international borders]]\n[[Category:Ethnic groups in Nepal|.]]\n[[Category:Ethno-cultural designations]]\n[[Category:Gurkhas|.]]\n\n\n{{Nepal-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{pp-move|small=yes}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{more references}}\n'''Nepalis''' (singular:'''Nepali''', synonym:'''Nepalese'''; {{lang-ne|\u0928\u0947\u092a\u093e\u0932\u0940}}) are the people associated with the country of [[Nepal]]. The term usually refers to the [[Nepali nationality law|citizens]] and nationals of Nepal, or the native speakers of the Nepali language. It is also used in reference to the people of Nepali origin or of ethnicities strongly associated with Nepal irrespective of their citizenship or native language.\n\n==Nepali citizens and nationals==\nNepali nationals number around 30 Million, with six million of them residing in India,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indembkathmandu.gov.in/page/about-india-nepal-relations/|title=Embassy of India, Kathmandu, Nepal : About India-Nepal Relations|website=www.indembkathmandu.gov.in|access-date=2020-04-17}}</ref> and one million more scattered around the world. They are multicultural, multiethnic and multilinguistic group that speak [[Languages 